From: yuukh <yuukh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: mediatek: keep PPE FPORT on all HNAT QDMA descriptors

CPU-to-Wi-Fi HNAT reinjection marks an skb for PPE0, but the existing
mtk_tx_map() override changes only the first QDMA descriptor.  Every
descriptor generated for an skb fragment is initialized afterwards with the
normal GMAC FPORT, producing an inconsistent descriptor chain for GSO/SG
traffic.

Remember that the skb is being reinjected and apply the PPE0 FPORT override
to every fragment descriptor as well.  Use the symbolic FPORT mask and PPE
port instead of the hard-coded values while touching the original override.

Signed-off-by: yuukh <yuukh@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c | 20 +++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c
@@ -1855,6 +1855,9 @@ static int mtk_tx_map(struct sk_buff *sk
 	struct mtk_tx_dma *itxd_pdma, *txd_pdma;
 	struct mtk_tx_buf *itx_buf, *tx_buf;
 	int i, n_desc = 1;
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_MEDIATEK_HNAT)
+	bool hnat_to_ppe = false;
+#endif
 	int queue = skb_get_queue_mapping(skb);
 	int k = 0;
 
@@ -1883,8 +1886,9 @@ static int mtk_tx_map(struct sk_buff *sk
 	txd_pdma = qdma_to_pdma(ring, txd);
-	#if defined(CONFIG_NET_MEDIATEK_HNAT) || defined(CONFIG_NET_MEDIATEK_HNAT_MODULE)
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_MEDIATEK_HNAT)
 	if (HNAT_SKB_CB2(skb)->magic == 0x78681415) {
-		txd->txd4 &= ~(0xf << TX_DMA_FPORT_SHIFT_V2);
-		txd->txd4 |= 0x3 << TX_DMA_FPORT_SHIFT_V2;
+		hnat_to_ppe = true;
+		txd->txd4 &= ~(TX_DMA_FPORT_MASK_V2 << TX_DMA_FPORT_SHIFT_V2);
+		txd->txd4 |= PSE_PPE0_PORT << TX_DMA_FPORT_SHIFT_V2;
 	}
 #endif
 
@@ -1922,6 +1926,16 @@ static int mtk_tx_map(struct sk_buff *sk
 
 			mtk_tx_set_dma_desc(dev, txd, &txd_info);
 
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_MEDIATEK_HNAT)
+			/* mtk_tx_set_dma_desc() restores the normal GMAC FPORT on
+			 * every SG descriptor.  Keep the whole reinjected packet on
+			 * the same PPE0 path as its first descriptor.
+			 */
+			if (hnat_to_ppe) {
+				txd->txd4 &= ~(TX_DMA_FPORT_MASK_V2 << TX_DMA_FPORT_SHIFT_V2);
+				txd->txd4 |= PSE_PPE0_PORT << TX_DMA_FPORT_SHIFT_V2;
+			}
+#endif
 			tx_buf = mtk_desc_to_tx_buf(ring, txd,
 						    soc->tx.desc_size);
 			if (new_desc)
